ted in the history of architecture in order to locate themselves and determine their own position? This volume discusses the history of architecture in the context of art history, and the relativity of writing histories of architecture is shown through four stories about the Who, What, How, and Why of architecture. This way, Andri Gerber can introduce an adequately structured theory of history - a »meta-history«, which creates knowledge that enables the architect to relate to history in his work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitekturgeschichte. 4aArchitekturtheorie. 4aIdeologie. 4aKritik. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aMetapher. 4aRaum. 4aUtopie. 4aWissenschaftsgeschichte. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh  aArchitectural Theory.  aArt History.  aCritique.  aHistory of Architecture.  aHistory of Science.  aIdeology.  aMetaphor.  aSpace.  aUtopia.1 aAlessi, Alberto.1 aHerres, Uli.1 aMeister, Urs.1 aSchurk, Holger.1 aStaub, Peter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts and Architecture 2014z9783110369595oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839429440zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839429440423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839429440/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DKAb2014  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016